<p>I came across this code , that matches the * wildcard against a string. * can be considered as 0 or more characters. </p>  <pre><code>def samePattern(main,pattern):     if pattern=="*" or main==pattern:         return True     if main=="":         return False     if main[0:1]==pattern[0:1]:         return samePattern(main[1:],pattern[1:])      if pattern[0:1]=="*":         return samePattern(main[1:],pattern) or samePattern(main,pattern[1:])      return False </code></pre>  <p>While I think I understood the base cases, I am not understanding how the line</p>  <pre><code>if pattern[0:1]=="*":         return samePattern(main[1:],pattern) or samePattern(main,pattern[1:]) </code></pre>  <p>is working. </p>  <p>Could anybody explain how it is working ?</p>